></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uberenfellhand.showPublicProfile?language=EN>BerenFellhand</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 26<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(6/8/02 6:44:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2113.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: XP Bonus and Negatives</span><hr size=1> I think you are dead on mate.<br><br>If I could make sure one thing was working the way it used to, this would be it.<br><br>Cheers,<br>Beren <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uiristreedawn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Iris Treedawn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 23<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(6/8/02 11:35:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2113.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: XP Bonus and Negatives</span><hr size=1> As I recall, the bonuses and penalties were always based on the order - disorder part of alignment.  I never really noticed them making much difference, even so.  I doubt that they expanded the exp bonus system to incorporate good and evil, but that's just my instinct.  <br><br>The cross-alignment grouping is the single change that I am most disappointed with on FV.  Happily, most people still seem to stick with their own when it comes to alignment. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=dalninil>Dalninil</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 4